radiographic_examinations.findings: Fluid-filled and dilated appendix up to 1.3 cm with mild wall hyperemia and surrounding fat stranding. A 1.0 x 0.8 cm appendicolith at the base of the appendix and a tiny appendicolith in the distal appendix. Subcentimeter cortical hypodensities bilaterally in kidneys likely represent cysts. Trace free fluid in the pelvis, likely reactive. A 1.2 cm cystic lesion in the midline of the prostate consistent with a prostatic utricle cyst. Visualized lung fields, liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, rectum, urinary bladder, and distal ureters within normal limits.
